Doggies or trucks?

16:03.329 --> 16:05.563
I don't deserve trucks.

16:05.565 --> 16:08.332
I'll be the judge of that.

16:08.334 --> 16:10.201
You deserve trucks.

16:11.971 --> 16:14.572
Damn. Anybody else
get hit with a geode?

16:14.574 --> 16:15.973
I got hit with a geode.

16:15.975 --> 16:17.908
Some dude stuck his
fingers in my mouth.

16:17.910 --> 16:20.478
What is that? Is that
like a desert power thing?

16:20.480 --> 16:21.979
When things started
escalating, I just rolled up

16:21.981 --> 16:23.914
into a little ball
like an armadillo.

16:23.916 --> 16:26.584
Fellas,
can I get real for a second?

16:27.820 --> 16:30.755
I was thinking
about Aly the entire time.

16:31.924 --> 16:34.825
This is one of her barrettes.

16:36.662 --> 16:38.262
You know, women use barrettes

16:38.264 --> 16:40.998
to keep their hairs in
different styles. Yeah.

16:41.000 --> 16:43.601
And Aly uses this to pin
her hair up when she's on duty.

16:43.603 --> 16:45.202
And I kept it.

16:45.204 --> 16:47.505
(chuckles)
That's how pathetic I am.

16:47.507 --> 16:48.606
That's not pathetic.

16:49.509 --> 16:50.541
It's lovely.

16:50.543 --> 16:54.278
It reminds me of all
my old lost loves.

16:54.280 --> 16:58.182
Yeah. Cece.

16:58.184 --> 17:00.184
Or my ex.

17:00.186 --> 17:01.685
She was a pill,

17:01.687 --> 17:04.021
but when she used to go
to second base on me,

17:04.023 --> 17:06.757
she was like Joe Morgan.

17:08.127 --> 17:10.628
You know, a lot of people
don't know this,

17:10.630 --> 17:15.032
but, uh,
Aly's full name is Alison.

17:16.702 --> 17:19.470
I like to imagine that she
was named after the song.

17:19.472 --> 17:21.439
♪ Alison ♪

17:22.375 --> 17:25.075
♪ I know this world ♪

17:25.077 --> 17:27.711
♪ Is killing you ♪

17:27.713 --> 17:31.048
♪ Alison ♪

17:31.050 --> 17:32.583
♪ Ba-ba-ba-ba-ba-ba ♪

17:32.585 --> 17:36.487
♪ My aim is true. ♪

17:36.489 --> 17:38.389
Sorry I got us
into this, Nick.

17:38.391 --> 17:39.890
I was useless out there.

17:39.892 --> 17:41.225
I didn't even get
one punch in.

17:41.227 --> 17:42.893
That's not true.
You hit me a little bit.

17:42.895 --> 17:44.562
I got my ass whomped out there.

17:44.564 --> 17:47.064
Got whomped up
and down the road.

17:47.066 --> 17:49.066
What's whomp?
Like a whomp-down.

17:49.068 --> 17:50.768
Oh, whooped?
Whomped.

17:50.770 --> 17:51.936
Are you talking
about getting beat up?

17:51.938 --> 17:53.571
Yes.
Whooped.

17:53.573 --> 17:54.772
I got this calendar bod,

17:54.774 --> 17:56.407
but it doesn't
hold up in battle.

17:56.409 --> 17:58.075
Look, it's 2016.

17:58.077 --> 18:00.077
She's not looking
for a strong husband.

18:00.079 --> 18:02.179
That... no, tha-that's
not what I was gonna...

18:02.181 --> 18:03.581
That's not where
I was going with this.

18:03.583 --> 18:06.517
I'm getting married, Nick.

18:06.519 --> 18:08.452
How am I going
to defend Cece?

18:08.454 --> 18:10.688
She deserves the best
husband in the world,

18:10.690 --> 18:13.190
and what if I don't
have what it takes?

18:13.192 --> 18:17.428
Of course you have what it
takes to be a modern husband.

18:17.430 --> 18:20.264
Do you have what it takes to be
a husband of the old world?

18:20.266 --> 18:21.599
God, no.

18:21.601 --> 18:24.101
They would use you as a pelt.

18:24.103 --> 18:27.004
Today, you fought, kinda.

18:27.773 --> 18:29.273
You're gonna make
a great husband to Cece.

18:29.275 --> 18:30.941
How do you know?
Because I know.

18:30.943 --> 18:32.810
Because why?
Because.

18:32.812 --> 18:34.645
Look what happened here today.
Because why?

18:34.647 --> 18:36.947
Beca... ever since I've
known you, you've been there.

18:36.949 --> 18:38.449
Okay, you're always there.

18:38.451 --> 18:40.818
Even when I don't want
you there, you're there.

18:40.820 --> 18:43.387
That's what a husband does.

18:43.389 --> 18:45.956
You fight for me.
That's what a husband does.

18:45.958 --> 18:47.124
You care about what I eat.

18:47.126 --> 18:48.792
That's what a husband does.

18:48.794 --> 18:50.294
You've cooked for me,
even when I don't ask.

18:50.296 --> 18:51.962
That's what a husband does.

18:51.964 --> 18:54.498
When I pass out, you comb my
hair so there's no knots in it.

18:54.500 --> 18:55.833
That's what a husband does.

18:55.835 --> 18:57.301
So, guess what.

18:57.303 --> 18:58.469
You're gonna be a great
husband to Cece because

18:58.471 --> 19:01.472
you're a great husband to me.

19:01.474 --> 19:03.140
So that's how I know.

19:03.142 --> 19:04.341
You're, you're
like my husband.

19:04.343 --> 19:06.010
You're like my wife, but...

19:06.012 --> 19:07.978
Yeah, so that's how I know.

19:10.750 --> 19:12.149
Thanks for saying that, man.

19:12.151 --> 19:13.751
Yeah, man.

19:23.996 --> 19:26.997
(gagging, coughing)

19:33.172 --> 19:35.506
I need this to be done, okay?

19:35.508 --> 19:38.609
Well, you can't take it back.
I heard you say it, Nick.

19:38.611 --> 19:40.844
(deep voice): Hey, hey, hey.
What you guys up to?

19:40.846 --> 19:42.780
We're pouring out one
for our lost loves.

19:42.782 --> 19:45.349
Good-bye, unrequited
love for Aly.

19:45.351 --> 19:48.185
May I now heal and,
and move forward.

19:48.187 --> 19:50.387
I'm proud of you, man.

19:50.389 --> 19:53.190
And as a gift, I'm gonna give
you your own property back.

19:53.192 --> 19:55.526
You don't have to do that.
I mean, it's not...

19:55.528 --> 19:57.127
I don't really need it, but...

19:57.129 --> 19:58.762
Whoa.

19:59.865 --> 20:02.366
Aly is single.

20:03.736 --> 20:05.302
Aly is single! Nice! Oh, great.

20:05.304 --> 20:06.737
Hey.
Hey.

20:06.739 --> 20:08.238
Okay, so are you gonna
tell her how you feel?

20:08.240 --> 20:09.373
I don't know. I don't know, uh,

20:09.375 --> 20:10.407
I don't know, I mean,

20:10.409 --> 20:11.542
what if she doesn't
like me back?

20:11.544 --> 20:12.710
What if I'm not
good enough for her?

20:12.712 --> 20:13.877
What if I can't bear her sons?

20:13.879 --> 20:15.112
You have to try.
Look, I didn't think

20:15.114 --> 20:17.081
I was good enough for Cece.
You aren't.

20:17.083 --> 20:18.549
Winston, I don't know how
this is going to work out,

20:18.551 --> 20:20.551
but you need to know
that you're good enough.

20:20.553 --> 20:22.553
You got a heart of gold.

20:22.555 --> 20:25.155
You got a smile that...
(groaning)

20:25.157 --> 20:27.257
He's been having some
really nice moments today

20:27.259 --> 20:28.559
and then kind of freaking out.

20:28.561 --> 20:29.827
You son of a bitch!

20:29.829 --> 20:31.762
So, what, you guys think
I should tell her how I feel?

20:31.764 --> 20:33.230
Yes. You absolutely should.

20:33.232 --> 20:34.398
Let's go now.

20:34.400 --> 20:35.566
What about your bachelor party?

20:35.568 --> 20:36.900
Who could want
anything more

20:36.902 --> 20:38.602
from a bachelor party
than their best friend

20:38.604 --> 20:40.904
telling him that they love him.
No. For real? You said that?

20:40.906 --> 20:42.573
I didn't tell him that I love
him. Let's be clear about that.

20:42.575 --> 20:44.074
I missed that?
You know what?

20:44.076 --> 20:45.275
I'm gonna tell Cece
how I feel about her.

20:45.277 --> 20:46.610
I'm gonna get her back.

20:46.612 --> 20:47.611
You do that, bud--
wait, wait.

